2011-04-28T03:31:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/spurs-beat-grizzlies-to-avoid-nba-playoff-elimination-heat-oust-76ers.html
The  San Antonio Spurs  beat the
 Memphis  Grizzlies 110-103 in overtime to avoid elimination from
the National Basketball Association playoffs.  Gary Neal made a 25-foot 3-point jumper as time expired for
the Spurs to tie the game at 97-97 and force overtime. San
Antonio heads to Memphis for Game 6 on April 29 trailing 3-2 in
the best of-seven-game playoff.    The series winner will face the  Denver Nuggets  or  Oklahoma
City  Thunder for a place in the Western Conference finals. The
Thunder lead the Nuggets 3-1 ahead of tonightâ€™s game in Oklahoma
City.  Also today, the  Miami Heat  beat the Philadelphia 76ers
97-91 to advance to a second-round meeting with the  Boston
Celtics  in the Eastern Conference.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
